      "RunningJobState": {
        "description": "The physical execution state of a job, as reported by the **supervisor**.\n\nThe supervisor is ground truth for what is *physically executing*. The\nswitchboard mirrors this into the `tml_switchboard.job_state` DB column and\nadopts it verbatim during reconciliation (case 4: the supervisor reports\n`OngoingJob(J_sb)` for the assigned job, so the DB takes the reported state).\n\n# Mapping to the DB `job_state`\n\nThe DB `job_state` enum (`switchboard/SCHEMA.sql`) is a superset of this one:\nit adds the switchboard-owned bookends `queued` and `scheduled` (before a\nsupervisor reports anything) and `finalized` (after termination). The\nassigned, supervisor-owned sub-states map one-to-one:\n\n| `RunningJobState`     | DB `job_state` |\n|-----------------------|----------------|\n| `Initializing{stage}` | `initializing` (+ `initializing_stage`) |\n| `Ready`               | `ready`        |\n| `Terminating`         | `terminating`  |\n| `Terminated`          | `finalized` (see below) |\n\n`Terminated` is **not** a 1:1 mapping: it folds into the terminal DB record\n`finalized`, which additionally requires a [`switchboard::TerminationReason`].\nA supervisor reporting `Terminated` always means a *workload-driven* exit, so\nthe switchboard finalizes it with `termination_reason = workload_exited`; the\nreason is implied by the report, not encoded in the variant, which is why\nthere is deliberately no total `RunningJobState → job_state` conversion. The\nworkload's [`TaskExitStatus`] is **not** carried here — it is reported\nout-of-band via [`SupervisorJobEvent::DeclareExitStatus`] whenever the\nsupervisor knows it, so by the time a job terminates the switchboard has\nalready recorded the outcome.\n\n# The retained-terminal contract\n\nA supervisor keeps reporting `Terminated` for a finished job — retaining it\nin memory as `ReportedSupervisorStatus::OngoingJob` — until the switchboard\nacknowledges it with [`SwitchboardToSupervisor::StopJob`], at which point the\nsupervisor drops the record and becomes `Idle`. This prevents a job that\ncompletes while the switchboard is disconnected from being misread, on\nreconnect, as a dropped job (which would spuriously trigger its restart\npolicy). The record is in-memory only: if the supervisor loses it (restart),\nit reports `Idle` and the job is legitimately classified as\n`supervisor_dropped_job`. See the worker's `reconcile` Rustdoc (case 4).\n\n[`switchboard::TerminationReason`]: crate::api::switchboard::TerminationReason",
        "oneOf": [
          {
            "description": "Starting up; `stage` mirrors the DB `initializing_stage`.",
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "stage": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/JobInitializingStage"
              },
              "state": {
                "type": "string",
                "const": "initializing"
              }
            },
            "required": [
              "state",
              "stage"
            ]
          },
          {
            "description": "Up and running (the workload is executing).",
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "state": {
                "type": "string",
                "const": "ready"
              }
            },
            "required": [
              "state"
            ]
          },
          {
            "description": "Shutting down; the next report is normally `Terminated`.",
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "state": {
                "type": "string",
                "const": "terminating"
              }
            },
            "required": [
              "state"
            ]
          },
          {
            "description": "The workload has exited. Drives the switchboard's `→ finalized`\ntransition (`termination_reason = workload_exited`). The workload's\noutcome is *not* carried here — it is reported out-of-band via\n[`SupervisorJobEvent::DeclareExitStatus`]. The supervisor retains this\nreport until the switchboard acks it with `StopJob` (see the type-level\nRustdoc).",
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "state": {
                "type": "string",
                "const": "terminated"
              }
            },
            "required": [
              "state"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "SupervisorStatus": {
        "description": "Note the difference with [`switchboard_supervisor`](super::switchboard_supervisor)'s\n[`SupervisorStatus`](super::switchboard_supervisor::ReportedSupervisorStatus): that one is concerned\nsolely primarily with over-the-wire communication, so it does not have 'Disconnected' variants.\nHowever, on the switchboard side, we do need those, hence the differrent set of variants.",
        "oneOf": [
          {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "job_id": {
                "type": "string",
                "format": "uuid"
              },
              "job_state": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/RunningJobState"
              },
              "status": {
                "type": "string",
                "const": "busy"
              }
            },
            "required": [
              "status",
              "job_id",
              "job_state"
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "job_id": {
                "type": "string",
                "format": "uuid"
              },
              "job_state": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/RunningJobState"
              },
              "status": {
                "type": "string",
                "const": "busy_disconnected"
              }
            },
            "required": [
              "status",
              "job_id",
              "job_state"
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "status": {
                "type": "string",
                "const": "idle"
              }
            },
            "required": [
              "status"
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "status": {
                "type": "string",
                "const": "disconnected"
              }
            },
            "required": [
              "status"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "TaskExitStatus": {
        "description": "The supervisor's report of how the user's workload is/has turned out — its\n*task outcome*.\n\nThe supervisor posts this at any point while it is assigned the job (see\n[`SupervisorJobEvent::DeclareExitStatus`]), independently of termination, and\nmay revise it: `Pending` while the result is not yet known, then `Success` or\n`Failure`. Once set it is never cleared (it can only move between these three\nvalues). It is orthogonal to *why* a job terminated (see\n[`switchboard::TerminationReason`]) — a job may carry any outcome regardless\nof its termination reason, or none at all if the supervisor never reported.\n\n[`switchboard::TerminationReason`]: crate::api::switchboard::TerminationReason",
        "oneOf": [
          {
            "description": "The workload is running; its result is not yet determined.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "pending"
          },
          {
            "description": "The workload completed successfully.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "success"
          },
          {
            "description": "The workload failed.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "failure"
          }
        ]
      },
      "TerminationReason": {
        "description": "Why a job terminated.\n\nThis records *why* a job stopped and is orthogonal to the\n[`TaskExitStatus`] (the success/failure of the user's workload) and to any\n`exit_message`. Mirrors the `tml_switchboard.termination_reason` DB enum.",
        "oneOf": [
          {
            "description": "The job's own workload ended it.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "workload_exited"
          },
          {
            "description": "The job requested its own cancellation.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "workload_self_canceled"
          },
          {
            "description": "Externally canceled by a user.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "user_canceled"
          },
          {
            "description": "Timed out while still queued.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "queue_timeout"
          },
          {
            "description": "Timed out while dispatched/executing.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "execution_timeout"
          },
          {
            "description": "The job's image was bad or could not be fetched (user fault).",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "image_error"
          },
          {
            "description": "No supervisor matched the job's tag configuration.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "supervisor_match_error"
          },
          {
            "description": "The supervisor/host failed to start the job.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "supervisor_host_start_failure"
          },
          {
            "description": "The supervisor dropped the job (lost on reconnect).",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "supervisor_dropped_job"
          },
          {
            "description": "The supervisor was unreachable.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "supervisor_unreachable"
          },
          {
            "description": "Resuming a previously started job failed.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "resume_failed"
          },
          {
            "description": "An unexpected internal failure.",
            "type": "string",
            "const": "internal_error"
          }
        ]
      },
      "WorkFilter": {
        "type": "string",
        "enum": [
          "idle",
          "busy"
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}
